tion, from young to mature.\n\n- Shepherd Hoodwin, Journey of Your Soul: A Channel Explores the Michael Teachings\n|\nWorry does not empty tomorrow of its sorrow, it empties today of its strength.” Corrie ten Boom\n\n- Corrie\n|\nI need Christ, not something that resembles Him.\n\n- C.S. Lewis, A Grief Observed\n|\nSomeday, even my existence would be felt.\n\n- Khadija Rupa, Unexpressed Feelings\n|\nIn the end, class will out. So much talk about helping the poor. It's all words and class interest— in the end.\n\n- Psyche\n|\nI want her back' I said 'I want HIM back'~Charlie\n\n- Ann M. Martin, Everything for a Dog\n|\nJames Tilly Matthews was not a prophet. He was a gifted, perhaps fragile individual who suffered intensely, and for little if any reward.\n\n- Mike Jay, A Visionary Madness: The Case of James Tilly Matthews and the Influencing Machine\n|\nWolves travel in packs, but the fiercest travel alone.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nThere is no smarter professor than life, and no wiser sage than experience.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nOur father knew more than any living person about the secret of time, except how to live in it. His time did not travel; it was a block of persisting nows.\n\n- Richard Powers, The Time of Our Singing\n|\nA heart like mine, which never got any kind of affection growing up, is terrible above all things.\n\n- Junot Díaz, The Brief Wondrous Life of Oscar Wao\n|\nKeep your innocence and ignorance aside, and expose yourself to dangerous situations, and understand the deeper secrets of life.\n\n- Michael\n|\nIt is necessary to grow up in maturity, firmness and courage in order to reach the goal\n\n- Sunday\n|\nNo air, no balloons!\n\n- Ljupka Cvetanova, The New Land\n|\nTime, which grays hair and wrinkles faces, also withers violent affections, and much more quickly.\n\n- Fernando Pessoa, The Selected Prose of Fernando Pessoa\n|\nIt is of men, and of them only, that one should always be frightened.\n\n- Louis-Ferdinand Céline, Journey to the End of the Night\n